data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
1. Hold your cube with the white face on top and the green face facing towards you.
2. If the bottom-right corner of the white face has white facing upwards (as shown in the diagram below (left)), perform U moves until the bottom-right corner of the white face does not have white facing upwards.
3. Perform the moves: R', D', R, D. Repeat this whole sequence until the bottom-right corner of the white face has white facing upwards.
4. Repeat steps 2 and 3 until all 4 corners have been completed, and the white face of the cube is solved, as shown in the diagram below (right).
Note: do not worry if other faces on your cube appear to be temporarily messed up. They will be resolved if you complete this whole stage correctly.
